LINEAR STEADY STATE CONDUCTION IN 123 DIRECTION WITH TET MESH

A basic heat conduction test in [0,1]^3 with a linear steady state solution.
Non-constant Dirichlet conditions on 3 adjacent faces of the cube and constant
flux conditions on the opposing faces that are consistent with the linear
steady state solution are imposed.  Here we are concerned with recovering the
steady state solution T = 1 + a*x + b*y + c*z, H = 2*T for a given direction
abc, and not not so much with the transient approach to steady state.

&MESH
  mesh_file = 'cube-tet.g'
/

&OUTPUTS
  output_t = 0.0, 500.0
  output_dt = 500.0
/

&PHYSICS
  materials = 'stuff'
  heat_transport = .true.
/

&DIFFUSION_SOLVER
  abs_temp_tol       = 0.0
  rel_temp_tol       = 1.0e-4
  abs_enthalpy_tol   = 0.0
  rel_enthalpy_tol   = 1.0e-4
  nlk_tol            = 0.05
  max_nlk_itr        = 6
  nlk_preconditioner = 'hypre_amg'
  verbose_stepping   = .true.
/

&NUMERICS
  dt_init = 1.0d-5
  dt_min  = 1.0d-7
  dt_grow = 10.0
  dt_max  = 100.0
/

ANALYTIC SOLUTION -- USE FOR DIRICHLET BC
&FUNCTION
  name = 'T-soln'
  type = 'polynomial'
  poly_coefficients = 1.0 1.0 2.0 3.0
  poly_exponents(:,1) = 0 0 0 0
  poly_exponents(:,2) = 0 1 0 0
  poly_exponents(:,3) = 0 0 1 0
  poly_exponents(:,4) = 0 0 0 1
/

&THERMAL_BC
  name = 'right/back/top'
  type = 'temperature'
  face_set_ids = 2, 4, 6
  temp_func = 'T-soln'
/

&THERMAL_BC
  name = 'left'
  type = 'flux'
  face_set_ids = 1
  flux = 1.0
/

&THERMAL_BC
  name = 'front'
  type = 'flux'
  face_set_ids = 3
  flux = 2.0
/

&THERMAL_BC
  name = 'bottom'
  type = 'flux'
  face_set_ids = 5
  flux = 3.0
/

&BODY
  surface_name = 'from mesh file'
  mesh_material_number = 1
  material_name = 'stuff'
  temperature = 1.0
/

&MATERIAL
  name = 'stuff'
  density = 4.0
  specific_heat = 0.5
  conductivity = 1.0
/
